Your current code is already doing the best practical thing for ETA:

Last 14 days history

Successful runs only

Ignore abnormal runs < 30 minutes

Median instead of mean

Remaining runtime for currently running DAG


There is no magic code change that will suddenly make the ETA accurate.

The biggest improvement you can make is:

Change 1: Increase lookback window

Replace:

LOOKBACK_DAYS = 14

with:

LOOKBACK_DAYS = 30

This gives more historical data and stabilizes the median.


---

Change 2: Show hours in CSV

Add below LOOKBACK_DAYS:

def minutes_to_hours(minutes):

    if minutes is None:
        return ""

    return round(minutes / 60, 2)


